  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "Configuring a universal remote typically involves a few key steps, though the exact process can vary depending on the model and brand of the remote. Here\u2019s a general guide to help you set up most universal remotes:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Gather Information**\n- **Device Codes**: Locate the code list for your remote. This is often found in the manual or on the manufacturer's website. You\u2019ll need the code for each device (TV, soundbar, DVD player, etc.) you want to control.\n- **Devices**: Know the make and model of the devices you want to program.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Power On the Device**\nTurn on the device (e.g., TV, soundbar, or DVD player) that you want to program the remote for.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Put the Remote in Programming Mode**\n- Press and hold the **SETUP** or **CODE SEARCH** button on the remote until the indicator light turns on.\n- Release the button.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Enter the Device Code**\n- Use the number buttons on the remote to enter the code for your device (from the code list).\n- The indicator light should turn off after entering the code.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Test the Remote**\n- Point the remote at the device and press the **POWER** button to see if the device turns off.\n- If it works, test other buttons (e.g., volume, input) to ensure full functionality.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Auto-Search (If the Code Isn\u2019t Known)**\nIf you don\u2019t have the device code:\n- Press and hold the **SETUP** or **CODE SEARCH** button until the indicator light turns on.\n- Press the **POWER** button repeatedly (while pointing at the device) until the device turns off.\n- Press **SETUP** or **ENTER** to save the code.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Repeat for Other Devices**\nRepeat the process for each device you want to control with the universal remote.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Sync with Smart Devices (For Advanced Remotes)**\nIf your universal remote supports Bluetooth or Wi-Fi:\n- Follow the manufacturer\u2019s instructions to pair it with smart devices (e.g., streaming sticks, smart TVs).\n\n---\n\n### **Troubleshooting**\n- **No Response**: Double-check the device code or try the auto-search method.\n- **Partial Functionality**: Some buttons may not work if the code isn\u2019t fully compatible. Try another code for the same device.\n- **Resetting the Remote**: If it\u2019s not working, try resetting the remote by removing the batteries for a few minutes or following the reset instructions in the manual.\n\n---\n\nIf you have the specific model of your universal remote, refer to its manual for more detailed instructions. Let me know if you need help with a particular brand!",
